# Aliro reader component options (ESP-IDF). Applies to every app that pulls the
# aliro_reader component (the standalone reader and the Matter lock).

menu "Aliro reader"

config WOZ_ALIRO_STEPUP
	bool "Enable the Aliro step-up (Access Document) phase"
	default n
	help
	  Reference-completeness build of the Aliro v1.0 §8.4 step-up phase: after
	  the standard EXCHANGE, the reader can request an ISO 18013-5 (mdoc) Access
	  Document from the User Device (ENVELOPE / GET RESPONSE APDUs carrying a
	  session-encrypted DeviceRequest/DeviceResponse), then parse and verify it
	  per §7.4 on a background worker.

	  This is OFF by default and, when on, is armed one-shot from the console
	  (`aliro-stepup arm`); it never runs per-unlock. The verification verdict is
	  logged and stored only -- it NEVER gates the unlock, which the provisioned
	  trust store alone decides. With this option unset the reader is byte-for-byte
	  identical to today and the fast-path auth segment is untouched.

endmenu
